body:
Hmm, this was not as easy as I thought:

In `build.DotNet.props` line 19, we still reference version 0.16:

```
    <Version>0.16.0</Version>
```

Also, in `ReefOnSpark.scala` line 31ff:

```
// Run:
// ..\spark\bin\spark-submit.cmd
//     --master yarn --deploy-mode cluster
//     --class org.apache.reef.examples.hellospark.ReefOnSpark
//     .\target\reef-examples-spark-0.16.0-SNAPSHOT-shaded.jar
```

The scala example can probably be fixed via a single commit. The `.props` file should be added to our python treatment.

@aloneguid Thanks so much for your interest! I'll try to explain my problem here (or we can continue our discussion on [JIRA-1773](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/REEF-1773)).

We would love to have a new feature in REEF that reads Parquet files, since Parquet format is very popular for machine learning and big data in general. Currently my implementation is very rudimentary - it calls a Java jar to read parquet files and dump that to disk. Then C# picks it up.

I'm wondering if there is a better pattern that I can follow. Thanks again.
